parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydraulic vacuum switch can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to a loss of braking power, especially in cold weather, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The brakes do not operate when the brake pedal is pressed
the brake pedal feels hard or spongy
the vehicle takes longer to stop than usual.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS electric pump can cause the vehicle to lose all braking power while driving, leading to a hard brake pedal and an inability to stop the vehicle, which can result in accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal becomes hard
the vehicle does not stop when the brake pedal is pressed
loss of braking power while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS system can cause a significant reduction in braking power, leading to an increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle takes longer to stop than usual
the brakes do not operate properly
the ABS system warning light is illuminated.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of headlights can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights shut off unexpectedly
all lights fail
including fog lights
headlights do not turn on in automatic mode
especially in cold temperatures (<20°F).

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic headlight system can cause reduced visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: Headlights do not turn on in automatic mode
especially in cold temperatures (<20°F)
headlights shut off unexpectedly
lack of predictable pattern in headlight failure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slipping or failed engagement can cause loss of power, hesitation, or sudden acceleration, leading to accidents or decreased vehicle control.
symptoms: The transmission slips or hesitates when shifting gears
the vehicle hesitates or lags when accelerating
the engine RPMs surge or fluctuate
the transmission makes unusual noises
such as grinding or whining sounds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the voltage regulator can cause an electrical failure in the engine compartment, leading to a fire, even when the vehicle is turned off, resulting in significant damage or total loss of the vehicle.
symptoms: Sudden electrical failure
smoke or flames from the engine compartment
battery explosion
acid spillage from the battery.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the battery can cause an explosion, leading to acid spillage and damage to the engine compartment, potentially resulting in a fire or total loss of the vehicle.
symptoms: Sudden battery explosion
acid spillage from the battery
smoke or flames from the engine compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine starting issue can cause inconvenience, delay, and potentially strand the driver, especially in emergency situations. This issue can also lead to increased wear and tear on the starter motor and battery.
symptoms: The engine starts sporadically
sometimes the vehicle starts and sometimes it doesn't
difficulty starting the engine
inconsistent engine cranking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: An engine compartment fire can cause damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries. It can also result in costly repairs or even total vehicle loss.
symptoms: Visible flames or smoke coming from the engine compartment
burning smell
overheating engine
engine warning lights or alarms.
